title: Tahir Iqbal wins NA-58 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) candidate Tahir Iqbal has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-58 Chakwal-I by securing 1,15,974 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was independent candidate Ayaz Amir, who bagged 1,02,537 votes.
The overall votersâ€™ turnout remained 62.05 percent.
